(4, 1, 1, 'Your professional journey is exciting but it will\nbe a challenge and in some parts it will not be \nsmoothe.   You will need to find out about your\npersonality and how you relate to the people\nyou study and work with – what you are good at\nand what seems hard and your best ways of learning\nall the different tasks \n\n<p>\nSee <a href="/pages/evidencing_your_practice_competencies/developing_yourself">Developing Yourself</a> to get started!</p>\n\n', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(5, 1, 1, 'Occupational therapists practice in many different\ncontexts and this is increasing with the advent of\nnew legislation and the emphasis on health and wellbeing\nand the management of people with chronic conditions.\nYour role will be different in each setting.  Your practice \nreasoning will become more thoughtful and specific as you develop \ninto a competent therapist. You will work differently  \nwith different groups of people and there will be different\nstarting points and different needs \n<p>See <a href="different_contexts">Different Practice Contexts</a> for more information...</p>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(6, 1, 1, 'As you go through your professional program you will\ndevelop as an occupational therapist.  We have designed\nthree levels to help you on this journey: 1) emerging, 2) consolidating \nand, 3) competent at graduation. Much will depend on your previous\nlife experiences and how you integrate these into your developing professional\nknowledge.  You will have prompts to guide you and many resources to help\nyou develop your competences.\n\n<p>See <a href="seven-steps">Seven Steps of Practice</a> to find out more about the individual steps.</p>\n\n<p>See <a href=''practice-resources''>Practice Resources</a> to access resources for each step.</p> \n\n<p>See <a href=''evidencing-practice''>Evidencing your practice competencies</a> for tools and guidance on evidencing your competence.</p> ', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(7, 1, 1, 'As you study and work as a developing therapist your thinking \nand practice reasoning guides what you plan and carry out with the people\nyou are working with.  This reasoning is also shaped by the context \nwhere you are working and who you are working with as well as the overall goal\nfor this service.  \n<p>\nSee the Practice Reasoning Frameworks within the seven steps of practice. [Note: this needs a new page to link to] \n</p>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(8, 1, 1, 'Some of you will want to carry out research studies on this work.\nThis section will give ideas to verify this work or take it further. \n<p>\nSee <a href=''research''>Possible Research Projects</a>\n</p>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(10, 1, 3, '<p>Occupational therapists work in many diverse areas of practice.  The way you work, who you work with and the goals of the organisation will all be different in these different contexts of practice.  You will find your practice thinking and reasoning will alter with each context, but the general, overall way you go about your practice, i.e. the principles and processes, will be similar and the Occupational Therapy Practice Process will guide you.</p>\n\n<object width=''780'' height=''540'' data=''/svg/practice-context.svg'' style=''margin: 0 auto; clear: both; display:block; border: thin solid darkgray; border-radius: 3px''></object>\n\n<p>These contexts are not mutually exclusive.  In many instances, when you work as an occupational therapist, you will cross over these boundaries and dip into another context.  For example, you might work in a school setting but need a splint to be made for a child, so you would go to the out-patients’ hospital to have it made. Usually one context predominates over the others. </p>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(11, 1, 4, '<p>In 2010 The Australian Minimum Competency Standards were published.  But when students were consulted on evidencing their competencies they requested that they be reconfigured into a framework that related to practice.  Therefore, the Occupational Therapy Practice Process was developed to represent the different aspects of practice and then the competencies were embedded in each step.  In addition, as practice reasoning is integral to being competent, each step has its own particular reasoning focus.  This configuration will help you to clearly relate your competencies as they develop to the different aspects of daily practice.</p> \n<!--[if lt IE 9]>\n<img src=''/svg/wheel.png'' width=''650'' height=''650''/>\n<![endif]-->\n\n<!--[if  !IE | (gte IE 9)]> <!-- -->\n<object id=''wheel'' type="image/svg+xml" \n    width="650" height="650" style="float:right; clear:right;" \n    data="/svg/wheel.svg">\n  </object>\n<!-- <![endif]-->\n\n<p>Use the Occupational Therapy Practice Process to ensure that you are developing your competencies in all the areas of practice, and also, at your level of professional development: </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Emerging</li>\n<li>Consolidating</li>\n<li>Competent to Graduate</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>You can use the interactive Occupational Therapy Practice Process on this website to access resources relative to each step of the process to help you develop your competence.   </p>\n\n<p>This framework can be used individually at each step for setting your learning objectives by using the prompts or the Occupational Therapy Competency Evidencing Matrix (OTCEM), or you can use it to self-evaluate your developing competencies using the OTCEM, or you can use it as a whole for developing a case study or a narrative.</p>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(12, 1, 6, '<p><b>Evidencing Your Practice Competencies</b></p>\n\n<p>This area is about YOU! It is situated at the Occupational Therapy Competency Evidencing Matrix (OTCEM). It is where you can continue to learn about yourself and to know yourself as you are becoming a competent graduate occupational therapist. It is here where you can assess yourself so you can determine what level in practice you are working at before you ask others to assess you. You will find you may be strong in some areas but you will need to do more work in other areas. </p>\n\n<p>Using the OTCEM, you will be able to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Self-assess your developing competence against:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>The steps of the Occupational Therapy Practice Process</p>\n\n</li>\n<li><p>Practice Themes</p>\n\n</li>\n<li><p>The 3 Competency Development Levels – Emerging, Consolidating &amp; Competent to Graduate</p>\n\n</li>\n<li><p>The OTCEM competency statements – which are mapped to the PRACSOT performance criteria containing the Occupational Therapy Australian Competency Standards (2010)</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Share your self-assessed OTCEM with your practice educator and university lecturer to verify your competence and provide feedback</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Add/upload supporting evidence – including documented and/or your written statement or explanation to support/show how you are competent as you have self-assessed at the relevant level</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Store, track and access your uploaded supporting evidence in your OTCA ePortfolio, which will contain a summary and history of your competencies</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Share your ePortfolio with your practice educator/supervisor and university lecturer for feedback and assessment</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Utilise the OTCEM observable behaviours providing a guide to meeting practice placement competence – your practice educator will also use the OTCEM observable behaviours to verify your competence</p>\n\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For further information about the competency development levels and types of evidence you can use to evidence your developing competence, see:<br>\n<a href="/docs/Occupational Therapy Competency Development Levels &amp; Levels of Evidence.pdf">Levels of Evidence &amp; Types of Evidence (PDF - 426 kB)</a></p>\n', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(13, 1, 5, '<p>The practice resources have been separated into the seven STEPS of the {ot-practice-process-link}. </p>\n\n<p>The following icons illustrate the type of resources you will find in each of these sections.</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/book.png'' alt=''Book'' class=''icon''></img> = Explanation text</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/video.png'' alt=''youtube video'' class=''icon''></img> = Video examples</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/ppt-icon32x32.png'' alt=''Powerpoint'' class=''icon''></img> = Presentations (Powerpoint)</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/audio.png'' alt=''Slides'' class=''icon''></img> = Audio files</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/quiz.png'' alt=''Quiz'' class=''icon''></img>= Quizzes to test your knowledge</p>\n\n<p><img src=''/img/web-link.png'' alt=''Anchor'' class=''icon''></img> = Links to sources on-line</p>\n\n', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(14, 1, 9, '<table>\n	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<th><p>\n					<b>Step 1: </b>\n				</p></th>\n			<th class=''nocheckbox''><p>\n					<b>Request for Service (RFS):<br>Emerging </b>\n				</p></th>\n			<th><p>\n					<b>Request for Service (RFS): Consolidating</b>\n				</p></th>\n			<th><p>\n					<b>Request for Service (RFS): Competent to Graduate</b>\n				</p></th>\n		</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td><p>\n					<b>Being efficient &amp; maintaining quality</b>\n				</p></td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6, 1.3.5''>Explains the RFS process at\n					team /service level and the policy on recording/ storage of client\n					information and maintaining confidentiality</p>\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6, 1.3.5''>Participates in the RFS process\n					at team /service level and the policy on recording /storage of\n					client information and maintaining confidentiality</p>\n\n\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6, 1.3.5''>Manages all aspects of RFS at\n					team/service level in a timely manner, implementing record\n					management policy and maintaining confidentiality</p>\n\n\n\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td rowspan="2"><p>\n					<b>Implementing professional standards</b>\n				</p></td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4, 3.2.1''>Explains non-discriminatory practice at the RFS step</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4, 3.2.1''>Demonstrates non-discriminatory practice and respects the\n					rights of the clients to refuse service - with assistance</p>\n\n\n\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4, 3.2.1''>Independently implements non-discriminatory practice and\n					respects the rights of the clients to refuse service</p>\n\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Discusses their practice reasoning at RFS with educator</p>\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning at RFS - with guidance\n				</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning appropriately and can\n					evidence good judgement and decision making at RFS</p>\n\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td><p>\n					<b>Collaborating with co-workers and others</b>\n				</p></td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5''>Describes the roles and responsibilities of other team\n					members or services at RFS</p>\n\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5''>Engages with co-workers or referrers developing professional\n					collaborative relationships appropriately</p>\n\n\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5''>Establishes collaborative professional relationships with\n					co-workers or referrers and manages conflicts with diplomacy</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td rowspan="4"><p>\n					<b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b>\n				</p></td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.3, 7.2.5''>Describes the parameters of the profession in this context</p>\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.3, 7.2.5''>Informs co-workers and clients on the scope of the\n					profession, and the role of the occupational practice educator in this context</p>\n\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.3, 7.2.5''>Modifies language or utilises different communication styles\n					for the listener when explaining occupational therapy in this context</p>\n\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1''>Describes professional communication methods used in this\n					setting at RFS when telephoning, giving instructions, writing, and\n					questioning</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1''>Communicates verbally and non-verbally with respect, empathy\n					, and clarity at RFS when: telephoning, giving instructions,\n					writing and questioning</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1''>Communicates verbally and non-verbally with respect, empathy,\n					clarity, when telephoning, giving instructions, writing,\n					questioning and in case discussions</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Describes the documentation policy at RFS and writes draft\n					case notes for educator</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Writes objective, concise and relevant case records or\n					reports at RFS to policy standard with guidance</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Writes objective, legible, concise, relevant case records\n					/reports to policy standard (sign-off by educator)</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n\n		<tr valign="TOP">\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2, 5.1.4''>Describes how communication is adapted to meet preferred\n					communication styles of the client</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2, 5.1.4''>Amends communication strategies to accommodate client’s\n					culture, language, sensory impairment, intellectual disability or\n					other communication styles - with guidance</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2, 5.1.4''>Adapts communication strategies to accommodate client’s\n					culture, language, sensory impairment, intellectual disability or\n					to meet individual communication styles</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(15, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th ><p><b>Step 2: </b> </p></th>\n<th><p><b>Information Gathering:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Information Gathering:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Information Gathering:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><b>Being client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,2.1.2,2.1.3''>Identifies what other information is required to proceed with the request for service</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,2.1.2,2.1.3''>Participates in the collection of relevant information with cognisance of client’s needs and service expectations </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,2.1.2,2.1.3''>Leads on the collection of relevant information regarding client’s needs, strengths and service expectations </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP">\n<td><p><b>Being Efficient and Maintaining Quality</b></p></td>\n<td>\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.1''>\nDescribes information gathering systems and their effectiveness\n</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.1''>\nParticipates in appropriate information gathering in a timely, efficient and effective manner\n</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.1''>\nTakes appropriate initiative and leadership in gathering relevant information in a timely, efficient/effective manner\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Implementing professional standards</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9''>Explains how confidentiality is maintained and consent managed when information gathering</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9''>Participates in appropriate information gathering gaining consent and maintaining confidentiality with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9''>Takes appropriate initiative and leadership in gathering information, gaining consent and maintaining confidentiality </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Identifies the thinking that contributes to decision making when information gathering</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Discusses practice reasoning when information gathering with educator</p>\n\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning appropriately and can evidence good judgement and decision making when gathering information</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Collaborating with co-workers and others</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.2.2''>Explains when information gathering, how the principles of occupation and health are promoted with co-workers</p>\n\n</td>\n<td><p data-pracsot=''3.2.2''>Participates in collaboration with co-workers, promoting the principles of occupation &amp; health when information gathering </p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.2.2''>Collaborates with co-workers, promoting the relationship between occupation &amp; health when information gathering</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,5.2.1''>Identifies the co-workers or stakeholders where collaboration is required to gather information</p>\n\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,5.2.1''>Contributes to case discussions, participating appropriately in collaboration with others when gathering information</p>\n\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,5.2.1''>Demonstrates being an appropriate team member and shows the ability to work in partnership with co-workers in formal and informal case discussions when info. gathering</p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Describes independently the sharing of information gathered with relevant team members and others </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Participates in sharing of information gathered with relevant team members and co-workers</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Initiates independently the sharing of information gathered with relevant team members and co-workers </p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="4" ><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2''>Describes communication methods when information gathering </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2''>Communicates clearly and concisely when gathering information introducing self, purpose of enquiry, information required and why, with guidance </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.2''>Communicates clearly and concisely when information gathering including introducing self, stating the purpose of enquiry, the information required and why it is required</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.3''>Identifies communication strategies used to respect diversity</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.3''>Uses effective communication strategies which respects diversity </p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.3''>Uses a range of relevant communication skills and identifies barriers to communication adapting strategies as required </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.3.3''>Describes appropriate verbal and non-verbal language which develops rapport when information gathering</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.3.3''>Uses appropriate verbal and non-verbal language to develop rapport</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.3.3''>Creates own professional communication style using "therapeutic use of self" to develop rapport </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Describes the documentation policy and writes draft case notes for educator</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes objective, concise and relevant case records or reports to policy standard with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes objective, legible, concise, relevant case records /reports to policy standard (sign-off by educator)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(16, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th ><p><b>Step 3: </b> </p></th>\n<th><p><b>Occupational Assessment:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Occupational Assessment:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Occupational Assessment:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="6" ><p><b>Being client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.2, 1.4.3, 1.5.1, 2.1.4, 2.1.1, 3.3.1, 3.3.7''>Observes how interviews and assessments target the client’s key occupational roles and occupations</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.2, 1.4.3, 1.5.1, 2.1.4, 2.1.1, 3.3.1, 3.3.7''>Participates in relevant interviews and assessments to target the client’s key occupational roles and occupations using an appropriate model of practice</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.2, 1.4.3, 1.5.1, 2.1.4, 2.1.1, 3.3.1, 3.3.7''>Selects and completes relevant interviews and assessments to target the client’s key occupations, occupational roles and environment using an appropriate model of practice</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.2,1.5.3,7.3.1''>Seeks best available evidence to interview/assessment selection </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.2,1.5.3,7.3.1''>Identifies best available evidence to interview/assessment selection with consideration of client preference</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.2,1.5.3,7.3.1''>Applies best available evidence to interview/assessment selection with consideration of client preference</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,2.1.4,3.3.1''>Explains the purpose of the interview process</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,2.1.4,3.3.1''>Participates in a systematic, appropriate and comprehensive interview - with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,2.1.4,3.3.1''>Administers systematic, appropriate and comprehensive client interviews (person, occupation and environment)</p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.3, 1.3.2, 2.1.5, 2.1.7''>Identifies client’s needs and understands their perspective</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.3, 1.3.2, 2.1.5, 2.1.7''>Listens actively, sensitively and respectfully to client’s needs/wants/priorities and desired outcomes</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.3, 1.3.2, 2.1.5, 2.1.7''>Listens actively to client’s perspectives integrating their needs/strengths/priorities and desired outcomes modifying approaches accordingly</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Explains and is aware of how privacy and comfort of the client is managed throughout the assessment </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Participates in ensuring the client’s privacy and comfort throughout the assessment process - with supervision</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Manages independently the client’s privacy and comfort before, during and after the assessment process</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.7''>Describes the outcome of assessment/s</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.7''>Participates in confirming the outcome of the assessment/s with the client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.7''>Confirms with the client the outcome of the assessment/s</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Being efficient &amp; maintaining quality</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Identifies risk assessment/strategies used to ensure both client/carer safety</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Applies risk management strategies to ensure client/carer safety</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Instigates and completes appropriate risk management strategies to ensure client / carer safety</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.6''>Identifies assessment selection and explains the results</p>\n</td>\n<td data-pracsot=''2.1.6''> \n<p>Reviews assessments used in this setting and interprets the results appropriately, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td data-pracsot=''2.1.6''> \n<p>Analyses assessment selection and interprets results appropriately identifying further assessments required</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Implementing professional standards</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Describes how informed consent is obtained</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Participates in gaining and recording informed consent</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Leads on gaining and recording informed consent</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9,1.2.5''>Describe non-discriminatory and culturally appropriate assessment/s</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9,1.2.5''>Participates in the selection of assessments which are culturally appropriate and non discriminatory </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9,1.2.5''>Selects assessments which are relevant, non-discriminatory and culturally appropriate </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4, 2.1.5, 2.2.2''>Discusses practice reasoning used in assessment selection with educator</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4, 2.1.5, 2.2.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning when selecting and administering assessment, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4, 2.1.5, 2.2.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning appropriately and evidences good judgement and decision making when selecting and administering assessment/s </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Collaborating with co-workers &amp; others</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1,1.4.4,3.2.2,5.4.2''>Explains how the principles of occupation for health and well-being are conveyed to team or stakeholders</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1,1.4.4,3.2.2,5.4.2''>Participates in advocating the principles of occupation for health and well-being to the team and other stakeholders</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1,1.4.4,3.2.2,5.4.2''>Advocates the principles of occupation for health and well-being to the team and other stakeholders</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Describes team processes, and works respectfully with co-workers, support workers or other co-workers on assessment/s</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Contributes to team meetings or co-worker communications professionally, and reports on assessments acknowledging the team role in client outcomes</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.2''>Contributes to team meetings or co-worker communications professionally, reporting on outcomes of assessments, giving opinions or judgements appropriately</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.5''>Identifies collaborative assessments and explains how information is disseminated</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.5''>Contributes to collaborative assessments with co-workers and participates in the dissemination of information </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.5''>Completes collaborative assessments with co-workers and disseminates information appropriately</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="6" ><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,2.1.2''>Describes the principles and purpose of the assessment process and develops rapport with clients </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,2.1.2''>Explains the principles and purpose of assessment to client, developing rapport and promoting collaboration</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,2.1.2''>Explains the purpose, content and duration of assessment to client, developing rapport and promoting collaboration </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.1''>Asks relevant questions during assessment </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.1''>Asks questions based on observation or the evidence base</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.1''>Asks relevant questions based on information provided, observation, model of practice or the evidence base </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1,5.1.4,5.2.3,1.1.5,1.1.6,5.1.3''>Communicates appropriately with clients, listens attentively and speaks without jargon, using appropriate language</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1,5.1.4,5.2.3,1.1.5,1.1.6,5.1.3''>Communicates appropriately with client, listens attentively, and speaks without jargon adapting the communication style as appropriate including participation in communication using an accredited interpreter</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.1,5.1.4,5.2.3,1.1.5,1.1.6,5.1.3''>Communicates appropriately without jargon and is able to adapt to diversity, including language, culture, gender, age or disability, including the use of accredited interpreters</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.1,2.1.2,2.1.5,2.1.7''>Explains how the client’s needs, priorities and desired outcome of intervention is sought in the assessment process</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.1,2.1.2,2.1.5,2.1.7''>Identifies and confirms with client their strengths, needs, priorities and desired outcomes of intervention is sought in the assessment process</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.1,2.1.2,2.1.5,2.1.7''>Identifies and confirms with client their strengths, needs and desired outcomes actively collaborating on what is realistic, achievable and relevant to the practice setting</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Describes the documentation policy and writes draft assessment notes for educator </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes objective, concise and relevant assessment records/reports to policy standard</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes objective, legible, concise, relevant assessment records/reports to policy standard (sign-off by practice educator)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6,5.2.6''>Explains data protection, and client access to records policy and how these are explained to the client</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6,5.2.6''>Communicates with client about how personal information will be recorded, stored and used with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6,5.2.6''>Communicates with client about how personal information will be recorded, stored and used within local policy</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(17, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th><p><b>Step 4: </b> </p></th>\n<th><p><b>Identification of Occupational Issues:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Identification of Occupational Issues:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Identification of Occupational Issues:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><b>Being Client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.4.2''>Identifies occupational issues in collaboration with client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.4.2''>Negotiates occupational issues clearly prioritising client’s preferences within scope of the service with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.4.2''>Negotiates occupational issues clearly prioritising client’s preferences within their strengths and the scope of the service</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><b>Being efficient and maintaining quality</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1,1.1.3,1.4.2,2.2.3,2.1.1,2.2.1,2.2.3,5.1.5''>Describes the occupational issues found and can identify those relevant to this setting</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1,1.1.3,1.4.2,2.2.3,2.1.1,2.2.1,2.2.3,5.1.5''>Lists the occupational issues found and can prioritise and identify those relevant to this setting - with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1,1.1.3,1.4.2,2.2.3,2.1.1,2.2.1,2.2.3,5.1.5''>Negotiates and creates, a prioritised list of meaningful occupational issues with appropriate consideration to cost, time and resources and scope of the service </p>\n\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td><p><b>Implementing professional standards</b></p></td>\n\n\n\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.2''>Discusses the practice reasoning used when identifying occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.2''>Articulates practice reasoning giving clear, logical reasons for concentrating on chosen occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning appropriately and can evidence good judgement and decision making when identifying and prioritising occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP">\n<td><p><b>Collaborating with co-workers and others</b></p></td>\n<td>\n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1''>Explains how the occupational practice educator advocates to co-workers or others the prioritised occupational issues.</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1''>Participates in advocating the needs of the client and can clearly discuss with others the agreed occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.7,1.4.1''>Advocates the needs of the client and can clearly discuss with others the agreed occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders </b> </p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,5.1.1''>Describes how occupational issues are prioritised with the client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,5.1.1''>Participates in the discussion of prioritisation of occupational issues with client and/or significant others with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.1.3,5.1.1''>Leads on the discussion and prioritisation of occupational issues with client and/or significant others </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.5''>Discusses the process of negotiation and conflict resolution in prioritising occupational issues</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.5''>Participates in communication of the outcome of assessment and negotiates with client when prioritising occupational issues - with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10,5.1.5''>Communicates the outcome of assessment and leads on the process of negotiation and conflict resolution in prioritising occupational issues </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Writes draft records or reports for educator to view</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Writes objective, legible, concise records/reports - with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.2.4''>Writes objective, legible, concise records/ reports/ descriptions of activities within policy/protocol</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(18, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th><p><b>Step 5:</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Goal Setting:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Goal Setting:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Goal Setting:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Being client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.1.4,1.3.2,2.3.1,5.1.5''>Describes how rights, values, beliefs and needs are respected in goal setting</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.1.4,1.3.2,2.3.1,5.1.5''>Demonstrates how client’s rights, values, beliefs and needs are sought and integrated into goals set, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,1.1.4,1.3.2,2.3.1,5.1.5''>Demonstrates how client’s rights, values, beliefs and needs are sought and integrated into occupational goals set </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1, 1.1.3, 1.1.7, 1.2.5''>Identifies how goals promote participation in occupations and are culturally relevant</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1, 1.1.3, 1.1.7, 1.2.5''>Evidences how the client is enabled and empowered through goals which are culturally appropriate and promote participation, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1, 1.1.3, 1.1.7, 1.2.5''>Evidences how the client is enabled and empowered through occupational goals which are culturally appropriate and promote participation</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><b>Being efficient and maintaining quality</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.3,2.3.4''>Describes the goal setting process in this service and its relationship to the parameters of service delivery based on assessment findings</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.3,2.3.4''>Participates in the negotiation of realistic goals for the service setting, including consideration of cost, time and availability of essential resource based on assessment findings</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.3,2.3.4''>Negotiates realistic meaningful occupational goals for the service setting, considering cost, time, and availability of essential resources based on assessment findings</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Implementing professional standards</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9''>Identifies own prejudices and the importance of being non-judgemental when completing goal setting</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9''>Evidences how non-judgemental and non-discriminatory approaches applied to goal setting, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.9''>Meets professional and ethical standards, including being non-discriminatory and non-judgemental when goal setting</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,2.2.2,2.3.3''>Articulates the practice reasoning used to set goals</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,2.2.2,2.3.3''>Discusses and uses practice reasoning when goal setting when creating an intervention plan, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,2.2.2,2.3.3''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning and can evidence good judgement and decision making when goal setting, and creating an intervention plan</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Collaborating with co-workers and others</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2, 3.7.2''>Explains the system of communicating goal setting with co-workers</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2, 3.7.2''>Contributes to communicating goal setting with co-workers part of a team, or at handover </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2, 3.7.2''>Leads on communicating goal setting with co-workers as a, part of a team, or at handover </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.1, 2.3.1, 3.4.3, 5.2.1, 7.1.5''>Describes the system of team goal setting</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.2.1, 2.3.1, 3.4.3, 5.2.1, 7.1.5''>Participates actively in team goal setting, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td><p data-pracsot=''2.2.1, 2.3.1, 3.4.3, 5.2.1, 7.1.5''>Formulates and prioritises in setting team goals</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6,2.2.1,2.2.3, 2.3.1, 2.3.2 ,2.3.4''>Describes the methods used to explain and negotiate specific and meaningful short and long term goals</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6, 2.2.1, 2.2.3, 2.3.1, 2.3.2, 2.3.4''>Participates in the negotiation of Specific, Measurable, Activity based, Realistically Time-framed goals (SMART) short and long term goals, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6, 2.2.1, 2.2.3, 2.3.1, 2.3.2, 2.3.4''>Completes the negotiation and justification of SMART short and long term goals with client or significant others </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2''>Writes draft record or reports for educator</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2''>Writes objective, concise records/reports descriptions of goals, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.2''>Writes professional, objective, legible, concise records/reports descriptions of goals within policy/protocol </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none');
INSERT INTO `exp_channel_data` (`entry_id`, `site_id`, `channel_id`, `field_id_1`, `field_ft_1`, `field_id_3`, `field_ft_3`, `field_id_4`, `field_ft_4`, `field_id_6`, `field_ft_6`, `field_id_7`, `field_ft_7`, `field_id_8`, `field_ft_8`, `field_id_11`, `field_ft_11`, `field_id_12`, `field_ft_12`, `field_id_13`, `field_ft_13`, `field_id_14`, `field_ft_14`) VALUES
(19, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th><p><b>Step 6: </b> </p></th>\n<th><p><b>Intervention:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Intervention:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Intervention:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</th><th colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan=''5''><p><b>Being client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.2, 1.4.2, 1.5.1, 2.3.3, 3.3.2''>Describes the application of models of practice when intervention planning</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.2, 1.4.2, 1.5.1, 2.3.3, 3.3.2''>Participates on ensuring the intervention plan is realistic for the client, within a model of practice and within the scope of the service</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.2, 1.4.2, 1.5.1, 2.3.3, 3.3.2''>Leads on applying client-centred models, ensuring the intervention plan is realistic for the client, and within the scope of the service</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.4,3.1.1,3.2.1,3.3.5,3.4.4''>Explains how the interventions meet the occupational goals that have been set</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.4,3.1.1,3.2.1,3.3.5,3.4.4''>Completes intervention ensuring that the activities are working towards achieving the set occupational goals, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''2.3.4,3.1.1,3.2.1,3.3.5,3.4.4''>Plans, directs and completes timely client-centred intervention ensuring that the activities are working towards achieving the set occupational goals </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.5, 3.3.6, 3.4.2''>Explains rehabilitative approaches and their grading</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.5, 3.3.6, 3.4.2''>Participates in rehabilitation interventions which are occupational, appropriately graded and meet identified goals </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.5, 3.3.6, 3.4.2''>Completes appropriate rehabilitation interventions which are occupational, appropriately graded, meet identified goals and relevant to work context</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP">\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.4''>Explains what is realistic frequency, intensity and duration of intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.4''>Participates in interventions, maintaining frequency, intensity and duration</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.4''>Completes interventions of appropriate frequency, intensity and duration</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.1,3.3.5,3.3.6,3.3.7,3.3.8,3.4.2''>Explains compensatory interventions and the relationship to task analysis and identifies safety issues in this process </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.1,3.3.5,3.3.6,3.3.7,3.3.8,3.4.2''>Participates in compensation interventions, including assistive devices or environmental adaptations based on task analysis which are safe and meet identified goals</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.1,3.3.5,3.3.6,3.3.7,3.3.8,3.4.2''>Completes appropriate compensatory interventions, including the provision of assistive devices/environmental adaptations based on task analysis which are safe, meet identified goals and relevant to the work context</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="6" >\n\n<p><b>Being efficient and maintaining quality </b> </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6,2.1.4,3.1.3,3.3.1, 3.3.7,3.3.12, 3.4.4''>Documents how interventions can be adapted or modified in this work context</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6,2.1.4,3.1.3,3.3.1, 3.3.7,3.3.12, 3.4.4''>Makes suggestions how the intervention can be adapted or modified (occupation/environment) for client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.6,2.1.4,3.1.3,3.3.1, 3.3.7,3.3.12, 3.4.4''>Adapts or modifies the intervention in consultation with client (occupation, environment, duration or frequency) </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1''>Describes how the client was motivated and given feedback throughout intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1''>Motivates and gives feedback throughout the intervention appropriately, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.1''>Motivates, empowers and gives feedback throughout the intervention appropriately </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,3.3.4,3.6.1''>Explains the importance of collaborating with significant others in the intervention process</p>\n</td>\n<td><p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,3.3.4,3.6.1''>Participates in intervention with significant others in a culturally appropriate manner</p></td>\n<td><p data-pracsot=''1.1.2,3.3.4,3.6.1''>Creates opportunity for significant others to fully participate in the intervention process in a culturally appropriate manner</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.1,1.5.2,2.3.3,3.3.2,7.3.1''>Explains evidence-based intervention to improve participation in meaningful and valued life roles</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.1,1.5.2,2.3.3,3.3.2,7.3.1''>Finds the best evidence for intervention in this context to improve participation in meaningful and valued life roles</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.1,1.5.2,2.3.3,3.3.2,7.3.1''>Applies the best available evidence to intervention plan/s to improve participation in meaningful and valued life roles</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1, 3.4.2, 7.1.6''>Describes the work-based systems for setting up, planning and delivering intervention/s</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1, 3.4.2, 7.1.6''>Completes the planning and set up of intervention/s appropriately administering established work-based systems, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1, 3.4.2, 7.1.6''>Leads, plans and directs the delivery or delegation of intervention administering established work-based systems demonstrating relevant pace and efficiency</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1,3.3.11,3.4.5''>Describes how risk/safety are assessed and managed</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1,3.3.11,3.4.5''>Completes relevant risk/safety assessments and remediates, with assistance</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.4.1,3.3.11,3.4.5''>Leads, plans and directs relevant risk/safety assessments, and remediates appropriately</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="5" ><p><b>Implementing professional standards</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Explains the health and safety processes completed throughout the intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Contributes to the health and safety processes considered throughout the intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Ensures that all health and safety procedures are completed throughout the intervention</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.8''>Explains how client safety and best practice apply to the creation, fabrication, purchasing and fitting of assistive technologies or devices </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.8''>Participates in the creation, fabrication, purchasing and fitting of assistive technologies or devices within best practice guidance/manufacturer’s instructions ensuring client safety</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.8''>Creates, fabricates, purchases and fits assistive technologies or devices within best practice guidance/manufacturer’s instructions ensuring client safety</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,3.3.2''>Articulates the practice reasoning used in intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,3.3.2''>Discusses and uses practice reasoning in intervention, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.4,3.3.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning and can evidence good judgement and decision making when completing intervention</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Explains the importance of informed consent</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Participates in gaining informed consent</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.5''>Leads on gaining informed consent</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4,1.1.9,1.2.2,1.2.5,3.1.1''>Describes how the practice educator is respectful to the client’s culture, gender, religion age or disability </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4,1.1.9,1.2.2,1.2.5,3.1.1''>Demonstrates a respectful approach to the culture, gender, religion, age or disability of the client, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.4,1.1.9,1.2.2,1.2.5,3.1.1''>Demonstrates a respectful approach to the culture, gender, religion, age or disability of the client when conducting an intervention</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Collaborating with co-workers and others</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.4,3.4.3,3.6.1,5.2.1''>Describes who to collaborate with on interventions and identifies key co-workers</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.4,3.4.3,3.6.1,5.2.1''>Participates in collaborative interventions, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.4,3.4.3,3.6.1,5.2.1''>Establishes collaborative interventions with teams or others </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.5,3.3.6''>Explains the principles of group work and group dynamics</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.5,3.3.6''>Participates in group work appropriately collaborating with co-workers being cognisant of group dynamics</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.1.2,3.3.5,3.3.6''>Plans, leads and directs group work appropriately, collaborating with co-workers, managing group dynamics</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,3.1.2,3.3.8,3.4.3''>Explains collaboration with co-workers when recommending or providing items or services</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,3.1.2,3.3.8,3.4.3''>Collaborates with co-workers when recommending or providing items or services, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.5,3.1.2,3.3.8,3.4.3''>Collaborates with co-workers when recommending or providing items including assistive devices or services and manages conflict appropriately</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="5" ><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.10, 5.1.2, 5.1.4, 5.2.3''>Describes what constitutes appropriate instructions for the intervention</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.10, 5.1.2, 5.1.4, 5.2.3''>Provides clear instructions verbally or in writing using appropriate media/language, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.10, 5.1.2, 5.1.4, 5.2.3''>Provides clear instructions verbally or in writing using a range of appropriate media/language </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes a draft documentation record for practice educator to review within local documentation policy</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes objective, legible, concise records/reports/ descriptions of intervention, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.3.1''>Writes professional, objective, legible, concise records/ reports/ descriptions of intervention within policy/protocol </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.4, 3.2.1, 3.2.2, 3.3.10''>Identifies principles of health promotion and occupational well-being for the client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.4, 3.2.1, 3.2.2, 3.3.10''>Participates appropriately communicating the principles of health promotion and occupational well-being to the client</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.4, 3.2.1, 3.2.2, 3.3.10''>Analyses and leads on communicating the principles of health promotion and occupational well-being to the client </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Describes how any risks to clients are communicated</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Communicates any risks however small appropriately to client throughout intervention, with supervision</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.11, 3.4.5''>Communicates and consults about any risks however small appropriately to client before, during or after intervention</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.1.3,3.3.3''>Describes how the practice educator is attentive and actively listens to client’s emotional and physical well-being when completing intervention </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.1.3,3.3.3''>Using "therapeutic use of self", is attentive and actively listens to client’s emotional and physical well being when participating in interventions</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.8,3.1.3,3.3.3''>Using "therapeutic use of self", is attentive and actively listens to client’s emotional and physical well being when leading on the delivery of interventions</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><br />\n</p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.3,3.3.10,5.2.3,5.4.2''>Describes how technology or other media is used as part of an intervention or to communicate with clients to promote well-being</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.3,3.3.10,5.2.3,5.4.2''>Participates in the use of technology or other media as part of an intervention or to communicate with clients on health promotion, injury prevention, and participation in occupations, service delivery or other issues to promote well-being</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.3,3.3.10,5.2.3,5.4.2''>Uses technology or other media as part of an intervention or to communicate with clients on occupational therapy including health promotion, injury prevention, and participation in occupations, service delivery or other issues to promote occupational well-being</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(20, 1, 9, ' <table> 	<colgroup>\n                 <col>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n		<col width=''252px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>PRACTICE THEMES</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n<th>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY PRACTICE PROCESS STEP<br> &amp; LEVEL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <th ><p><b>Step 7: </b> </p></th>\n<th><p><b>Evaluation:<br>Emerging</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Evaluation:<br>Consolidating</b></p></th>\n<th><p><b>Evaluation:<br>Competent to Graduate</b></p></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>&nbsp;</td><td colspan=''3''>Competency Statements</th>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td ><p><b>Being client-centred</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.12,3.7.1, 4.1.1''>Describes the process of evaluating intervention with clients</p>\n\n\n\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.12,3.7.1, 4.1.1''>Participates in the evaluation of intervention with the client </p>\n\n\n\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.12,3.7.1, 4.1.1''>Evaluates intervention with the client including achievements and barriers to achievement of goals </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="3" ><p><b>Being efficient and maintaining quality</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9, 3.5.1, 3.5.2, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.2.2, 4.2.3, 4.4.1,5.3.2''>Reports on informal/formal evaluation methods or outcome measures used within local policy/protocol, and their relationship to recommendations to others</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9, 3.5.1, 3.5.2, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.2.2, 4.2.3, 4.4.1,5.3.2''>Participates in informal/formal evaluation methods or outcome measures within local policy/protocol making recommendations as needed, maintaining confidentiality </p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9, 3.5.1, 3.5.2, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.2.2, 4.2.3, 4.4.1,5.3.2''>Completes informal/formal evaluation or outcome measures within local policy/protocol making recommendations as needed, maintaining confidentiality</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6''>Describes discharge or cessation of intervention in accordance with protocol/policy with the client</p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6''>Participates in discharge or cessation of intervention within protocol/policy with the client, with assistance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''5.1.6''>Leads on discharge or cessation of intervention in accordance within protocol/policy with client consent on sharing information with others</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP">\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.2, 4.1.3, 4.3.1, 4.4.1, 4.4.3, 4.4.2, 4.4.3, 4.4.4''>Describes gaps or possible service developments as a consequence of evaluation </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.2, 4.1.3, 4.3.1, 4.4.1, 4.4.3, 4.4.2, 4.4.3, 4.4.4''>Participates in the identification of gaps or service developments as a consequence of evaluation, and with assistance can identify service developments</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.2, 4.1.3, 4.3.1, 4.4.1, 4.4.3, 4.4.2, 4.4.3, 4.4.4''>Identifies gaps or service developments as a consequence of evaluation and makes recommendations for service developments within organisational priorities </p>\n\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="2" ><p><b>Implementing professional standards </b> </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.2,1.5.3, 3.3.12, 4.1.4, 4.2.1, 4.2.2, 4.4.2, 4.4.7''>Describes evaluation methods used throughout Occupational Therapy Practice Process using some relevant evidence</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.2,1.5.3, 3.3.12, 4.1.4, 4.2.1, 4.2.2, 4.4.2, 4.4.7''>Participates in continuous self evaluation throughout the Occupational Therapy Practice Process using reflection and available evidence</p>\n</td>\n<td data-pracsot=''1.4.3,1.5.2,1.5.3, 3.3.12, 4.1.4, 4.2.1, 4.2.2, 4.4.2, 4.4.7''> \n<p>Evaluates self and intervention throughout the Occupational Therapy Practice Process utilising best available evidence and reflection</p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.2.3, 4.4.2''>Discusses the practice reasoning used at evaluation</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.2.3, 4.4.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning used at evaluation with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.2.3, 4.4.2''>Articulates and uses practice reasoning appropriately and can evidence good judgement and decision making when completing evaluation </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan="4"><p><b>Collaborating with co workers and others</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.1, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.1.3, 4.1.4, 4.2.3, 7.1.5''>Reports on the evaluation strategies used with co-workers appropriately</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.1, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.1.3, 4.1.4, 4.2.3, 7.1.5''>Participates in evaluation strategies with co-workers appropriately</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.1, 4.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.1.3, 4.1.4, 4.2.3, 7.1.5''>Implements evaluation strategies with co-workers appropriately </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.4, 3.6.1, 3.7.1, 3.7.2''>Explains the decision making process when intervention is ceased with clients, teams or others </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.4, 3.6.1, 3.7.1, 3.7.2''>Participates in the decision making to cease intervention or handover with clients, teams or others </p>\n\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.4, 3.6.1, 3.7.1, 3.7.2''>Liaises with clients, teams and others when making decision to cease intervention or handover to others </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2,5.2.2''>Describes the service network for this service</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2,5.2.2''>Identifies referral systems to other co-workers or services</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2,5.2.2''>Refers on to other co-workers or services appropriately</p>\n\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.2, 5.2.4''>Explains the principle processes of handover </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.2, 5.2.4''>Handovers casework to others appropriately, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.2, 5.2.4''>Handovers casework to others to practice/policy standard</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> <td rowspan=''3''><p><b>Communicating with client/s and stakeholders</b></p></td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.4.6, 4.4.8''>Describes the documentation policy at Evaluation and writes draft case notes for policy educator</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.4.6, 4.4.8''>Writes objective, legible, concise and relevant case records or reports to policy standard, with guidance</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3, 4.4.6, 4.4.8''>Writes objective, legible, concise, records/reports/discharge summaries independently to policy standard (sign-off by practice educator)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2, 4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Reports on the information given to the client and other stakeholders on leaving the service</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2, 4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Participates in the provision of relevant information to the client or relevant stakeholders on leaving the service</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.5.1,3.5.2, 4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Leads on the provision of relevant information to client or other relevant stakeholders on leaving the service</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3,4.3.3,4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Describes the importance of sharing the evaluation outcomes as part of professional development</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3,4.3.3,4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Participates in sharing evaluation outcomes as part of professional development with facilitation by educator</p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''3.7.3,4.3.3,4.4.6,4.4.8,5.3.2''>Shares appropriately the outcomes of evaluation of intervention to others as part of professional development</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(52, 1, 9, '<table class=''bap''>\n	<colgroup>\n		<col width=''292px''>\n		<col width=''292px''>\n		<col width=''292px''>\n	</colgroup>\n	<tbody>\n<tr><th><p><b>Being a Professional:<br>Lifelong learning</b></p>\n\n</th>\n<th><p><b>Being a Professional:<br>Professional behaviour</b></p>\n</th>\n<th><p><b>Being a Professional:<br>In the Workplace</b></p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n<tr><td colspan=''3'' class=''nocheckbox'' style=''background-color: #FFB510''><p><b>Generic competencies: to be met at all levels</b></p><p>Each competency statement is to be ticked off when you demonstrate that competency consistently and professionally.</p></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=''3'' style=''background-color: #852CBA; color: #FFF''>Competency Statements</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign="TOP"> \n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.6,  1.6.1, 6.1.1''>Seeks information or assistance appropriately when required</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.2.1, 1.7.1, 6.1.3''>Responds appropriately to suggestions, or feedback and creates a plan of action.</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.6.1, 4.3.3''>Participates actively in supervision </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.2.1, 1.2.3, 1.2.6, 6.1.3''>Has insight into own strengths, abilities and issues that need to be developed/worked on  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.5''>Prioritises professional development towards the skills required to fulfil the occupational therapist role in this work context </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.6.1, 6.1.1''>Proactively seeks a range of relevant professional development opportunities</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.2.2, 1.2.3, 1.2.4''>Researches the history and culture of clients appropriately </p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.1,1.8.1,1.8.2,4.1.4,6.1.3''>Appraises critically own performance</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''6.1.1''>Formulates professional development goals and works consistently on these goals to develop skills</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''5.4.1,6.1.2,6.21,6.2.2''>Shares new knowledge with others</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''6.2.1''>Can explain models and theories to others</p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''6.1.2,6.2.1,6.2.2''>Contributes to other student’s learning</p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.2.1,1.2.3,1.2.6''>Is aware of his/her own culture and its impact on the client through ongoing reflection/reflexivity. </p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.5.3,4.2.2,4.4.4, 5.4.1,6.1.2,7.3.1''>Evidences critical review of research to inform daily evidence based practice  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.2''>Participates in research for the advancement of the profession.</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.3,5.2.5,5.2.6,5.4.1,6.2.2,7.2.3''>Maintains ethical and professional conduct when using technology for practice, sharing information or for recording professional development </p>\n</td>\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.3,1.7.1,7.2.1 ''>Works within bounds of competency appropriate for the OT role in this context</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.1''>Acts with integrity and honesty and compassion </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Advises educator if ill or unable to fulfil duties safely</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.3''>Maintains professional boundaries with clients </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.5, 1.2.4, 1.2.6, 1.7.7''>Respects diversity, recognising and managing power imbalances appropriately </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''3.3.9''>Maintains confidentiality  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.1,7.1.3,7.1.4''>Manages time efficiently or effectively</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.3''>Adapts to change </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.6, 1.7.7''>Upholds the core values of the profession</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.4,1.8.1, 4.1.3,4.3.1,4.3.2,4.4.1, 4.4.5,7.3.2''>Critically appraises service delivery systems and proposes improvements were appropriate </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.8.1,4.2.1,4.3.1, 4.3.2,4.4.2,4.4.3,4.4.4,4.4.5,7.3.2''>Contributes to quality assurance and service developments  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.6 ''>Demonstrates appropriate self care strategies </p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.1,1.3.3, 1.7.3 ''>Works to international professional occupational standards at graduation level </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.2.2, 1.3.4, 1.7.3, 3.4.1, 5.2.5, 5.2.6, 7.2.1''>Adheres to workplace legislation including equal opportunities, anti discrimination etc</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.1,1.7.6,4.3.2,4.3.3''>Demonstrates an understanding of political legal and industrial issues that impact on the occupational therapy profession</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.5,1.2.4,1.4.4,1.7.7''>Applies principles of occupational and social justice  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.1.10, 1.3.6''>Is professional under duress and applies both stress management and conflict resolution strategies appropriately  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.6,1.8.3,5.4.2''>Participates in professional activities aimed at promoting the profession in university or placement </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.7''>Considers financial cost effectiveness when making recommendations for services or resources</p>\n</td>\n\n<td> \n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Arrives fit to work </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Telephones and speaks to appropriate staff when absent advising return to work details </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2 ''>Arrives punctually and leaves at agreed time</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Wears ID badge to practice protocol </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Observes dress code and dresses appropriately</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.2''>Prepares work appropriately </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.4,3.3.3,7.2.3''>Communicates appropriately to all clients, co-workers, staff and practice educator  </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.3''>Greets people appropriately on formal and informal occasions </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.2 ''>Completes all work place administration to required standard set by practice educator including recording of complaints </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.1,7.1.3,7.1.4, 7.2.2''>Works efficiently and effectively to workplace pace/timeframes </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.2''>Follows through on agreed actions or commitments  </p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.4, 7.1.7''>Respects work space and shares work space appropriately </p>\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.4, 3.3.3, 7.2.3''>Speaks on the phone respectfully and takes messages factually, clearly, with relevant details, date, time, signed</p>\n\n<p data-pracsot= ''5.2.5''>Maintains work based protocols on use of computer/mobile phones</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.3,7.2.1,7.2.4''>Complies with organisational health and safety requirements</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.4''>Complies with all systems in workplace which contribute to a safe working environment for all </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.3.4,4.4.3,4.4.5,4.4.7,7.2.5''>Demonstrates congruence with service priorities, strategic directions and goals </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.7,7.2.4''>Manages work resources appropriately including set up, tidy up of work areas and maintaining resource systems</p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.2.2,7.1.4''>Manages workload allocated by educator </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''1.7.4,4.1.2,7.1.6''>Skills and expertise of team members, including support staff are recognised, respected and utilised to maximum benefit to effective and efficient service delivery </p>\n\n\n<p data-pracsot=''7.1.6''>Is an effective team member to the benefit of the client </p>\n</td>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none');

